snippet.textDisplay:
Peter Wright shows how great person he is. They also proclaim him being a good man IRL too. Shy, but very good hearted. For so long time he was the "forever runner-up." But now he has the world title. And nobody can discard this fact. This may be his only world cup, might be one of his very few titles, but it's his. And it's the most important. Peter Wright officially has engraved his name in the history of darts.

He also is the oldest darts player to become a world champion for first time. Unless we count BDO, Martin Adams beats him by a few months I think. He anyways is a late bloomer in terms of darts. I think the only greater late bloomers are Gary Anderson (both were born in the same year) and Raymond van Barneveldt.

snippet.textDisplay:
MVG REALLY needs to improve his tripple 20. Thats what I think. If he can hit the first tripple 20 which he misses so many times, it gives him confidence and makes it SO much easier to hit 1-2 more tripples and better chance to hit 140-180. Usually he misses the tripple 20 and hits a LOT of tripple 19´s. He is by far the best at tripple 19 BUT he usually hits them after the first dart misses. It may not be possible but maybe its time to change the first throw? Then again it will change the tripple 19´s so who knows if its possible.


He played REALLY weak in the semis and final, and today he got punished BIG time, missing so many doubles he looked either nervous or weak, something mentally prob at key moments. Of course he lost the final, Peter didnt and cant win it if MVG plays up to his best, but he didnt and Wright yeah punished him and won comfortably.


Hope MVG takes it to the next level on the first dart. That will ensure he will be able to crush opponents in the future as he is used to, look how easy Wright made the 140´s look he threw the tripple 20s in like it was practice.
